  "text": "To assess habit strength, the Self-Report Habit Index (SRHI; [CITATION_1] was used. This index consists of 12 items based on three postulated features of habits, i.e. a history of repetition, automatic in nature and expressing identity. On a 5-point scale, children were asked to what extent they agreed (+2) or disagreed (-2) with different statements (e.g. 'exercise is something that is a part of my daily routine'; Cronbach's a = 0.77). Furthermore, data were collected on grade, gender and ethnicity. If the child or one or both parents was born outside the Netherlands, the child was classified as being of foreign origin.",
